      "test_id_raw": "prismvul.python.exec",
      "test_name_raw": "prismvul.python.exec",
      "judge_verdict": "TP",
      "judge_reason": "The code calls `exec(script, ...)` where `script` is user-controlled input. The `validate_script` function is broken: it returns True if ANY whitelisted function name appears in the script, and the `isalnum()` check would reject any expression with operators or parentheses. More critically, `exec` and `eval` are themselves in the whitelist, so an attacker can trivially bypass any intended restriction. The restricted globals (`{\"__builtins__\": {}}`) are insufficient because `exec` can still access builtins through other means (e.g., `().__class__.__bases__[0].__subclasses__()`). This is a true positive code injection vulnerability.",
